Package org.anchoranalysis.feature.calculate

Sub-feature units of calculation that can be cached.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    InitializableFeature<T extends FeatureInput>
    A feature that should be initialized with FeatureInitParams (or a sub-class) before any calculations occur.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    FeatureCalculation<S,T extends FeatureInput>
    Caches the result of a feature, until FeatureCalculation.invalidate() is called.
    FeatureCalculationMap<S,T extends FeatureInput,U,E extends Exception>
    Similar to a FeatureCalculation but stores several evaluations parameterised by a key.
    FeatureInitParams
    Parameters used to initialize a feature before any calculations
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    FeatureCalculationException  
    NamedFeatureCalculateException
    A feature-calculation exception that occurs in a particular named feature, or else a general message of failure.
